3. **Thread:** "Nonstick pan died after 6 months - what am I doing wrong?" - [Thread URL](http://localhost:9999/threads/3)  
   - **Forum:** /f/Cooking  
   - **Score:** 189  
   - **Comment Count:** 67  
   - **Top-Voted Take:** Most nonstick pans fail prematurely because users heat them on high with nothing in them, damaging the coating.  
   - **Classification:** technical_question

4. **Thread:** "Dutch oven comparison: Le Creuset vs Staub vs Lodge" - [Thread URL](http://localhost:9999/threads/4)  
   - **Forum:** /f/Cooking  
   - **Score:** 312  
   - **Comment Count:** 98  
   - **Top-Voted Take:** Le Creuset is better for light-colored foods and visual appeal, Staub excels at browning, and Lodge offers 80% of the performance at 20% of the cost.  
   - **Classification:** comparison

5. **Thread:** "Why does my stainless steel pan stick everything?" - [Thread URL](http://localhost:9999/threads/5)  
   - **Forum:** /f/Cooking  
   - **Score:** 278  
   - **Comment Count:** 102  
   - **Top-Voted Take:** Stainless steel requires proper preheating and the Leidenfrost effect test before adding oil to achieve nonstick properties.  
   - **Classification:** technical_question

6. **Thread:** "Chef knife under $100 that will last a lifetime" - [Thread URL](http://localhost:9999/threads/6)  
