### Sub-forum: /f/AskCulinary

9. **Thread:** "How to properly season a cast iron skillet?" - [Thread URL](http://localhost:9999/threads/9)  
   - **Forum:** /f/AskCulinary  
   - **Score:** 423  
   - **Comment Count:** 134  
   - **Top-Voted Take:** Use grapeseed or flaxseed oil, apply thin layers, bake at 450°F for one hour, and repeat 3-4 times for best results.  
   - **Classification:** technical_question

10. **Thread:** "Why does my Le Creuset Dutch oven have cracks in the enamel?" - [Thread URL](http://localhost:9999/threads/10)  
    - **Forum:** /f/AskCulinary  
    - **Score:** 198  
    - **Comment Count:** 56  
    - **Top-Voted Take:** Enamel cracking is typically caused by thermal shock from placing a hot pot on a cold surface or under cold water.  
    - **Classification:** technical_question

11. **Thread:** "Best cutting board material for knife longevity?" - [Thread URL](http://localhost:9999/threads/11)  
    - **Forum:** /f/AskCulinary  
    - **Score:** 267  
    - **Comment Count:** 89  
    - **Top-Voted Take:** End-grain wood cutting boards are significantly more knife-friendly than plastic or bamboo, preserving edge sharpness longer.  
    - **Classification:** technical_question

12. **Thread:** "Can I use metal utensils on my Scanpan?" - [Thread URL](http://localhost:9999/threads/12)  
    - **Forum:** /f/AskCulinary  
    - **Score:** 145  
    - **Comment Count:** 34  
    - **Top-Voted Take:** While Scanpan claims metal utensil safety, repeated use will still degrade the nonstick coating over time.  
    - **Classification:** technical_question

13. **Thread:** "Difference between braising and stewing?" - [Thread URL](http://localhost:9999/threads/13)  
    - **Forum:** /f/AskCulinary  
    - **Score:** 189  
    - **Comment Count:** 45  
    - **Top-Voted Take:** Braising uses less liquid and larger cuts of meat, while stewing fully submerges smaller pieces in liquid.  
    - **Classification:** technical_question

14. **Thread:** "How to fix a warped stainless steel pan?" - [Thread URL](http://localhost:9999/threads/14)  
    - **Forum:** /f/AskCulinary  
    - **Score:** 123  
    - **Comment Count:** 28  
    - **Top-Voted Take:** Warped pans cannot be effectively repaired and should be replaced, as they will cause uneven heating on flat cooktops.  
    - **Classification:** technical_question

